{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"18e0e7e5-9e52-4eac-a126-b5f050ae5ab7","content":"`.testsettings` files are **not supported in MSTest v3**. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's how each setting maps:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout` | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` |\n| Code coverage DataCollector | `<DataCollectors>` section |\n| `AssemblyResolution / useLoadContext` | No longer needed (default behavior) |\n\nLet me create the replacement `.runsettings` file and update the project:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01W18uBRKSVYGHfmFJCRGtmM","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01PXYgNo4yfaR59hPkVnDzb5","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-0ee9a7ee56de4cc2803b56338f8d0318/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.CoverageCollectorDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral\" />\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-0ee9a7ee56de4cc2803b56338f8d0318/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"7c78de1b-c3ee-474b-9dcf-50a99af8ddac","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file with three key configurations:\n\n1. **Test deployment** - `AssemblyResolution` with `useLoadContext=\"true\"` \n2. **Test timeout** - `TestTimeout` set to 30000ms (30 seconds)\n3. **Code coverage data collector** - Microsoft CodeCoverage\n\nIn MSTest v3, `.testsettings` files are no longer supported. The configuration needs to be migrated to a `.runsettings` file and/or MSTest attributes/properties in the `.csproj`.\n\nLet me explain how to migrate each setting:\n\n\nFor test timeouts, I can use the `[Timeout]` attribute directly on test methods or configure a default in `.runsettings`. Code coverage gets set up as a data collector in the same file. The assembly resolution with `useLoadContext` is now the default behavior in modern MSTest, so that part doesn't need explicit configuration. I'll create a `.runsettings` file to replace the old `.testsettings`.","outputTokens":712,"requestId":"040E:D4088:164DB4F:17B8D6F:6A033768"},"id":"ff858284-d1b5-4c50-8d23-ff4990788c70","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:21:44.879Z","parentId":"cb07bc89-a499-4114-97c5-e1dc50539ee1"}
